{
  "text": "Adiponectin acts via phosphorylation of 5'adenosine monophosphate-activated protein kinase (AMPK) to influence insulin sensitivity and fatty acid and glucose utilisation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Its action is mediated through the AdipoR1 and AdipoR2 receptors [CITATION_3] that are both expressed in cardiac tissue [CITATION_4] . Receptor activation is associated with modulation of AMPK, PI3K, p38 MAP kinase and extracellular signal-regulated kinase (Erk) 1/2 MAP kinase [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
